entry.title: The Civil Enforcement of Parking Contraventions (County of West Sussex) (Adur District) Designation Order 2009
entry.summary: This Order designates the area described in paragraph (2) of article 2 as a civil enforcement area in respect of parking contraventions, and as a special enforcement area, for the purposes of Part 6 of the Traffic Management Act 2004.

entry.title: The Civil Enforcement of Parking Contraventions (County of Derbyshire) Designation Order 2009
entry.summary: This Order designates the area described in the Schedule as a civil enforcement area for parking contraventions, and as a special enforcement area, for the purposes of Part 6 of the Traffic Management Act 2004.

entry.title: The Income Tax Act 2007 (Amendment) Order 2009
entry.summary: This Order exercises powers conferred by the Income Tax Act 2007 to undo changes and to make consequential amendments. The Acts affected are the Income and Corporation Taxes Act 1988 (article 2), the Taxation of Chargeable Gains Act 1992 (article 3), the Finance Act 1994 (article 4) and the Income Tax Act 2007 itself (article 5).

entry.title: The Feeding Stuffs (England) (Amendment) Regulations 2009
entry.summary: These Regulations further amend the Feeding Stuffs (England) Regulations 2005 (SI 2005/3281 as already amended by S.I. 2006/113, S.I. 2006/2808, S.I. 2006/3120, S.I. 2007/3008 and S.I. 2008/1523) (“the Feeding Stuffs Regulations”).

entry.title: The Water (Prevention of Pollution) (Code of Good Agricultural Practice) (England) Order 2009
entry.summary: This instrument applies in England and approves, under section 97(1) of the Water Resources Act 1991, the Code of Good Agricultural Practice to protect water, soil and air quality which was issued by the Secretary of State in January 2009 (“the 2009 Code”), so far as it was issued for the purpose mentioned in Article 2.

entry.title: The A52 Trunk Road (A46 Newark to Widmerpool Improvement and Slip Roads) Order 2009
entry.summary: This Order authorises improvements to the existing A52 and the construction of new lengths of trunk road and slip roads to provide a new junction with the A46. The route of the new trunk road is about 0.72 kilometres in length, from a point on the A52 Trunk Road, about 660m west of the centre of the existing Saxondale Roundabout at Saxondale in the County of Nottinghamshire, easterly to a point about 50m west of the centre of the existing Saxondale Roundabout.

entry.title: The Wireless Telegraphy (Register) (Amendment) Regulations 2009
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Wireless Telegraphy (Register) Regulations 2004 (S.I 2004/3155 as amended by S.I. 2006/340, S.I. 2006/1808, S.I. 2007/381, S.I. 2007/3389, S.I. 2008/689, S.I. 2008/2104 and S.I. 2008/3193) (“the Principal Regulations”).

entry.title: The A52 Trunk Road (A46 Newark to Widmerpool Improvement and Slip Roads) (Detrunking) Order 2009
entry.summary: This Order authorises the detrunking of a length of the existing A52 Trunk Road, between a point on the A52, 660m west of the centre of the existing Saxondale roundabout, to a point about 50m west of the existing Saxondale roundabout.

entry.title: The Wireless Telegraphy (Limitation of Number of Grants of Crown Recognised Spectrum Access) Order 2009
entry.summary: This Order specifies frequencies for which the Office of Communications (“OFCOM”) will grant recognised spectrum access.

entry.title: The A46 Trunk Road (Newark to Widmerpool Improvement and Slip Roads) Order 2009
entry.summary: This Order authorises improvements to the existing A46 Trunk Road and the construction of new lengths of trunk road and slip roads, to provide a largely dual carriageway between Newark and Widmerpool, east of Nottingham.

entry.title: The General Chiropractic Council (Constitution of the Statutory Committees) Rules Order of Council 2009
entry.summary: This Order approves Rules of the General Chiropractic Council (GCC) relating to the constitution of its four statutory committees: the Education Committee; the Investigating Committee; the Professional Conduct Committee; and the Health Committee.

entry.title: The Wireless Telegraphy (Crown Recognised Spectrum Access) Regulations 2009
entry.summary: These Regulations provide for the circumstances of use for which grants of recognised spectrum access may be made by the Office of Communications (“OFCOM”) to the Crown.

entry.title: The General Chiropractic Council (Registration of Chiropractors with United Kingdom Qualifications that are not Recognised Qualifications) Rules Order of Council 2009
entry.summary: This Order approves Rules of the General Chiropractic Council (GCC) in respect of registration on the basis of qualifications awarded by institutions in the United Kingdom prior to 15th June 2001, where an applicant practised as a chiropractor before 15th June 2001, has not practised as a chiropractor in the United Kingdom on or after 15th June 2001, has a good reason for not having made a successful application for registration during the transitional period after the statutory register held by the GCC was opened, and is capable of the competent and safe practice of chiropractic.

entry.title: The Wireless Telegraphy (Recognised Spectrum Access and Licence) (Spectrum Trading) Regulations 2009
entry.summary: These Regulations are made under section 30(1) to (3) of the Wireless Telegraphy Act 2006.

entry.title: The A46 Trunk Road (Newark to Widmerpool Improvement and Slip Roads) (Detrunking) Order 2009
entry.summary: This Order authorises the detrunking of a length of the existing A46 Trunk Road, between the lengths described below.

entry.title: The Non-Domestic Rate (Scotland) Order 2009
entry.summary: This Order prescribes a rate of 48.1 pence in the pound as the non-domestic rate to be levied throughout Scotland in respect of the financial year 2009–2010. A rate of 45.8 pence in the pound was the figure prescribed by the Scottish Ministers as the non domestic rate to be levied throughout Scotland for the financial year 2008–2009 (S.S.I. 2008/32).

entry.title: The 5875-5905 MHz Frequency Band (Management) Regulations 2009
entry.summary: These Regulations implement in the United Kingdom the Commission Decision 2008/671/EC of 5th August 2008 on the harmonised use of radio spectrum in the 5875-5905 MHz frequency band for safety-related applications of Intelligent Transport Systems (ITS) (the Commission Decision).

entry.title: The Copyright (Certification of Licensing Scheme for Educational Recording of Broadcasts) (Educational Recording Agency Limited) (Amendment) Order 2009
entry.summary: A licensing scheme operated by The Educational Recording Agency Limited (“ERA”) was certified for the purposes of section 35 of, and paragraph 6 of Schedule 2 to, the Copyright, Designs and Patents Act 1988 (1988 c.48) (“the Act”) by the Copyright (Certification of Licensing Scheme for Educational Recording of Broadcasts) (Educational Recording Agency Limited) Order 2007 (S.I. 2007/266) (as amended by S.I. 2008/211) (“the 2007 Order”).

entry.title: The Rural Development Contracts (Rural Priorities) (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2009
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Rural Development Contracts (Rural Priorities) (Scotland) Regulations 2008 (“the 2008 Regulations”) which introduce measures to supplement Council Regulation (EC) No. 1698/2005 (O.J. No. L 277, 21.10.2005, p.1) (“the Council Regulation”) which lays down general rules governing Community support for rural development (financed by the European Agricultural Fund for Rural Development established by Council Regulation (EC) No. 1290/2005 (O.J. No. L 209, 11.8.2005, p.1)) and Commission Regulation (EC) Nos. 1974/2006 (O.J. No. L 368, 23.12.2006, p.15) and 1975/2006 (O.J. No. L 368, 23.12.2006, p.74) laying down detailed rules for the application of the Council Regulation.

entry.title: The Conservation (Natural Habitats, etc.) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2009
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Conservation (Natural Habitats etc.) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1995 (“the 1995 Regulations”) which make provision for implementing Council Directive 92/43/EEC on the conservation of natural habitats and of wild fauna and flora (“the Habitats Directive”) (O.J. No L206, 22.7.92, p.7).
